OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1778810610
OL,3,CPaul Brand investigates how criminals
OL,4,Care exploiting the UK's waste system.
OL,6,FOver 1.2 million fly tips were
OL,7,Freported across the UK last year, a 9%
OL,8,Fincrease on the year before. This
OL,9,Fdramatic increase isn't being just
OL,10,Fdriven by the standard white van man,
OL,11,Fserious organised crime groups are now
OL,12,Falso operating in the waste sector,
OL,13,Flooking to exploit the system and make
OL,14,Fmillions in the process and leaving
OL,15,Fcatastrophic environmental damage in
OL,16,Ftheir wake.
OL,18,FThe Environment Secretary Emma
OL,19,FReynolds told Tonight:
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1778810610
OL,3,CPaul Brand investigates how criminals
OL,4,Care exploiting the UK's waste system.
OL,6,F"We've seen an increase in the serious
OL,7,Fand organised crime groups that are
OL,8,Finvolved in waste crime, and then they
OL,9,Fare using the proceeds of waste crime
OL,10,Fto fund their other illegal activity,
OL,11,Fwhether that's gun running or drug and
OL,12,Fhuman trafficking."
OL,14,FWith large sums of money to be made by
OL,15,Forganised crime groups, huge illegal
OL,16,Fdumps thousands of tonnes in size have
OL,17,Fbeen discovered across the country and
OL,18,Fquestions have been asked about how
OL,19,Fthey grew so large in the first place.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
