OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1778810610
OL,3,CPaul Brand investigates how criminals
OL,4,Care exploiting the UK's waste system.
OL,6,FThe Environment Agency told Tonight:
OL,7,F"People are becoming more
OL,8,Fsophisticated, so it wouldn't be
OL,9,Funusual for criminals to scope a site
OL,10,Fout that's masked by trees to put
OL,11,Fsignage up to say that there's maybe a
OL,12,Flegitimate construction operation
OL,13,Fgoing on."
OL,15,FIn Wigan, 25,000 tonnes of waste was
OL,16,Fdumped just metres from peoples homes,
OL,17,Fwith far reaching impacts.
OL,19,FWigan resident Nicha told the
OL,20,Fprogramme:
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
